bright expressions on their faces.</i>

102
00:11:22,136 --> 00:11:23,695
Are you a refugee as well?

103
00:11:24,038 --> 00:11:26,166
Yes. From Czechoslovakia...

104
00:11:27,308 --> 00:11:29,436
You say that you
know the children?

105
00:11:30,277 --> 00:11:31,472
Please let me see them.

106
00:11:32,112 --> 00:11:33,637
Just one look.

107
00:11:36,650 --> 00:11:38,175
Even just their
sleeping faces.

108
00:11:59,173 --> 00:12:01,835
A tragedy occurred
that night...

109
00:12:06,013 --> 00:12:07,640
<i>One girl is confirmed
to be alive!</i>

110
00:12:07,815 --> 00:12:09,044
<i>A man and a woman
are dead!</i>

111
00:12:09,116 --> 00:12:11,175
<i>The boy is in serious condition
but he has a pulse!</i>

112
00:12:11,385 --> 00:12:11,977
<i>Where's the patient?!</i>

113
00:12:12,119 --> 00:12:13,587
<i>Blood pressure, 72/50...</i>

114
00:12:13,687 --> 00:12:15,052
<i>Pulse, 138!</i>

115
00:12:15,522 --> 00:12:16,956
<i>The bullet went in
through his forehead?!</i>

116
00:12:22,263 --> 00:12:23,492
<i>Kill...</i>

117
00:12:29,303 --> 00:12:33,672
I didn't know what in the world
had happened.

118
00:12:34,975 --> 00:12:37,444
No. I knew.

119
00:12:38,078 --> 00:12:41,981
I knew everything,
but I ran away.

120
00:12:45,386 --> 00:12:50,256
I stopped thinking about
anything and ran away.

121
00:12:52,559 --> 00:12:54,653
I tried to draw.

122
00:12:55,863 --> 00:13:00,232
Pictures of those ideal twins...
Of them surrounded by love...

123
00:13:00,868 --> 00:13:05,396
But. ..no matter how many I drew,
I couldn't draw it.

124
00:13:07,775 --> 00:13:12,576
Because I knew that
it didn't exist.

125
00:13:18,185 --> 00:13:21,644
